The Alex Jones Show
Monday, 25 April 2011


[sebaygo1]


Scheduled Guests
................

From the Infowars web site ::

On this important Monday edition of the Alex Jones Show, top economist and columnist Paul Craig Roberts joins the show to discuss the latest revelations out of the IMF including a report indicating that China's economy will surpass the U.S. by 2016. Wayne Madsen will join Alex in-studio to discuss his decision to leave the country. 

Alex will discuss the latest on the TSA, the collapse of the U.S. dollar, ongoing fighting in Libya, and more.

Wayne Madsen visits in-studio in the later part of today's show. Today's broadcast extends about 30 minutes into a 4th hour "overdrive." Madsen will be in-studio with Alex again tomorrow.
